# URL-level excludes for the `lint / links` (lychee) check, read additively on
# top of the local lychee.toml. Each line is a regex matched against the
# (resolved) link. Skeleton/template FILES are excluded wholesale via
# `exclude_path` in lychee.toml; these patterns cover the remaining
# by-design / CI-hostile links.

# External pages valid for human readers but unreliable for the CI crawler —
# statuses/timeouts not in the accept list: the FCC page returns an HTTP/2 error,
# insta.rs intermittently returns 503, awwwards.com stalls until timeout.
https://www\.fcc\.gov/engineering-technology/laboratory-division/general/equipment-authorization
https://insta\.rs
https://www\.awwwards\.com
